    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
            <ab>
                <lb n="1"/>In 
                <lb n="2"/>se senes
                <lb n="3" break="no"/>cat<choice><corr>i</corr><sic>e</sic></choice>s </ab></div>
            
            <div type="translation">
            <p>“May you grow old in yourselves.”</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
            <p>Line 3: The original spelling of cates makes no sense, and thus was corrected to
                    cat´i`s. This object has no interpuncts or clear demarcation between words.
                    However, it makes the most sense to construe senes as being completed by
                    cat´i`s, and thereby creating a 2nd person plural subjunctive. This then allows
                    for se to be read with in and interpreted as a plural accusative. This, when
                    combined with the verb, is still an unusual formulation, but it can be construed
                    as “in yourselves.” The Boston MFA chose to translate this as “together.”</p>
                <p>The
                    words are placed running along the roundel, at the leftmost, uppermost, and
                    rightmost points. There is space at the bottom for another word, since the
                    torsos of the figures are cut off before the bottom.</p></div>
            

